<HEADLINE>
<P>
OPERATION RESCUE AND POLL ON ABORTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Times Poll and the article by George Skelton ("Most Americans Think 
Abortion Is Immoral," Part I, March 19) reveals the extent to which Americans 
have lost their way. 
</P>
<P>
The first paragraph was a corker! "Most Americans consider abortion to be 
immoral -- in fact, 'murder.' But they also believe deeply that each woman 
should be allowed to decide for herself whether or not to have an abortion." 
</P>
<P>
Do those two ideas in tandem not show a paralysis of analysis or what? 
</P>
<P>
We have all observed the popular practice of settling all issues so that 
everyone's brand of nonsense and evil is accommodated -- but this is not 
necessarily about the issue of abortion, but about the ability to keep our 
thinking straight. 
</P>
<P>
ROBERT GRIFFIN 
</P>
<P>
Whittier 
</P>
</TEXT>
