<HEADLINE>
<P>
OPERATION RESCUE AND POLL ON ABORTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I found article regarding the profile of the typical woman who has an abortion 
very refreshing ("Many in Survey Who Had Abortion Cite Guilt Feelings"). I was 
not surprised to read that the majority of women who have abortions are college 
educated, career women, who make over $40,000 per year. This runs totally 
contrary to the feminist, pro-choice, pro-abortion rhetoric of the past 20 
years. 
</P>
<P>
We have been told that abortion must be available to low-income, minority women 
so they can break the cycle of poverty and ignorance caused by unwanted and 
poorly timed pregnancies. The truth is that minority women place a higher value 
on life than do feminist and pro-choice advocates. 
</P>
<P>
Further, the poll showed that an overwhelming majority of Americans believe 
that abortion as a convenient form of birth control is just plain wrong. 
</P>
<P>
SEAN McCARTHY 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
