<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taylor Resigns From Citadel: Citadel Holding Corp. reported that James A. 
Taylor has resigned as chairman, chief executive and president of the 
Glendale-based firm. Taylor advised Citadel that, among other things, health 
reasons and the advice of his physician formed the basis for his actions. 
Taylor also resigned from the same positions he held at Fidelity Federal 
Savings &amp; Loan Assn., Citadel's wholly owned subsidiary. Taylor will 
continue to serve as a director on both the Citadel and Fidelity boards. Vice 
Chairman Edward L. Kane will succeed Taylor as chairman of the respective 
boards. Samuel C. McCarver, executive vice president, chief operating officer 
and chief financial officer of Citadel and Fidelity, was designated managing 
officer of both companies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
