<P>
HECHT PICKED AS ENVOY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush announced Friday that he is nominating former Nevada Sen. Chic 
Hecht to be ambassador to the Bahamas. Hecht was defeated in November by 
Nevada's Democratic Gov. Richard H. Bryan. 
</P>
