</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
FROM MOUNTAINS TO DESERT, FROM FORESTS TO SEA, A LIFT FOR SPIRITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
1. Mt. Calvary Episcopal Monastery, Santa Barbara. Run by Order of the Holy 
Cross monks. 20 acres in hills above city; sweeping coastline view. Open 
weekdays for individuals or groups; five chapel services daily. Will close for 
renovations June 1-Dec. 31. (805) 962-9855. 
</P>
<P>
2. La Casa de Maria, Montecito. Ecumenical. 26-acre densely wooded grounds. 
Individual retreats Wednesdays through Sundays; groups up to 150 for spiritual, 
educational and psychological purposes. (805) 969-5031. 
</P>
<P>
3. The Ojai Foundation, Ojai. Founded in the tradition of the late India-born 
philosopher Jiddu Krishnamurti; emphasizes Eastern, Native American 
spirituality. Forty acres of semi-wilderness. Work-retreat school and programs 
plus weekday and weekend retreats, events. (805) 646-8343. 
</P>
<P>
4. Camp Ramah, Ojai. Affiliated with the University of Judaism. Weekend 
retreats for those interested in Judaism; six scholar-in-residence weekends; 
summer children's camps. (213) 476-8571. 
</P>
<P>
5. Camp El Camino Pines, Frazier Park. Lutheran. Thirty acres on national 
forest land. Many recreational facilities; RV/tent sites. Groups from 30 to 130 
by day or week. (818) 367-8784. 
</P>
<P>
6. The Oaks, Lake Hughes. Sponsored by World Impact Inc. Nestled in a 130-acre 
secluded valley. Year-round; camps and retreats for groups, churches. (805) 
724-1018. 
</P>
<P>
7. Brandeis-Bardin Institute, Santa Susana. For Jews of all backgrounds. 
Setting is 3,100 acres of rolling hills; features the "House of the Book." 
Theme weekends; day programs with scholars in residence; workshops in music, 
drama and Israeli dance. (805) 526-1131. 
</P>
<P>
8. St. Andrew's Priory, Valyermo. Roman Catholic monastic community of the 
Benedictines. High desert. Individuals or groups up to 36 on weekdays; seasonal 
weekend retreats; youth retreats. Breakfast in silence; daily noon Mass, 
Vespers. (805) 944-2178. 
</P>
<P>
9. Paradise Springs, Valyermo. Interdenominational. In Angeles National Forest. 
All types of retreats; many recreational facilities. Families, groups up to 45, 
plus outdoor accommodations for up to 200. (805) 944-4500. 
</P>
<P>
10. Serra Retreat House, Malibu. Run by Roman Catholic Franciscan friars. 
Twenty-seven acres, overlooks ocean. Individual retreats, groups to 92 during 
weekdays; weekend retreats booked by parishes. Mass daily at 7:15 a.m. (213) 
456-6631. 
</P>
<P>
11. Campus by the Sea, Santa Catalina Island. Affiliated with InterVarsity 
Christian Fellowship. At the mouth of rugged canyon; sheltered beach. Sponsors 
family, college, youth camps; rental for groups from 25 to 100 in winter, 200 
in summer. Open March 1-Dec. 15. (213) 510-0015. 
</P>
<P>
