<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST : LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
MAN ACCIDENTALLY SLAIN BY POLICEMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Gardena police officer accidentally shot and killed a 20-year-old man who 
apparently ran into the line of fire as the officer shot at an armed drug 
suspect during an early morning drug raid, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The shooting occurred when officers tried to serve arrest warrants on a group 
of suspects living at a Budlong Avenue apartment in Gardena, Police Sgt. John 
Moore said. As the officers entered the apartment, Moore said, one of the 
suspects, armed with a shotgun, ran out of a bedroom and aimed the weapon at an 
officer. 
</P>
<P>
"This other man came running down the hallway just as the officer fired and he 
intersected the line of fire and was hit," Moore said. The man with the shotgun 
then dropped the weapon. 
</P>
<P>
The dead man was identified as Dexter Herbert. 
</P>
<P>
Officers arrested eight people in the apartment on suspicion of narcotics sales 
and murder. They were not identified. 
</P>
</TEXT>
