<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST : LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
ACTOR TODD BRIDGES PLEADS INNOCENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actor Todd Bridges pleaded innocent Friday to charges that he tried to kill a 
narcotics dealer by shooting him eight times in a drug-induced fit of violence 
in a cocaine rock house. 
</P>
<P>
Bridges, 23, of Sun Valley, the former child star of the now-canceled NBC-TV 
sitcom "Diff'rent Strokes," denied a single count of premeditated attempted 
murder at his Superior Court arraignment. 
</P>
<P>
If convicted, Bridges could be sentenced to life in state prison. Judge David 
Horowitz ordered Bridges to remain in custody in lieu of $2-million bail but 
agreed to consider a defense motion April 14 to lower that bail. 
</P>
<P>
Bridges was ordered earlier this week to stand trial on the charge after 
convicted narcotics dealer Kenneth Clay testified at a preliminary hearing that 
the actor shot him eight times inside a South-Central Los Angeles cocaine rock 
house Feb. 2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
