<TEXT>
<P>
Rob Milo pitched a one-hitter and had eight strikeouts to lead Laguna Hills 
High School to a 6-0 victory over San Dimas in the first game of a nonleague 
baseball doubleheader Friday at Laguna Hills. 
</P>
